Interface Map<K,V>

Type Parameters:

All Known Implementing Classes:
MyMap
public interface Map<K,V>
Interface representing a data structure for a map that stores key-value pairs. Each key in the map is unique, and a value is associated with each key. This interface offers basic operations such as adding elements, removing elements, retrieving values by key, checking if a key exists, and obtaining a list of all keys. Implementations of this interface should provide:
  • Adding elements by key and value, with the possibility of overwriting an existing key's value.
  • Removing elements by key.
  • Retrieving the value associated with a given key.
  • Checking if a given key exists in the map.
  • Generating a string representation of the map in the format "key=value".
